## 2. Parameters (0.0-10.0)

All parameters use the standard 0.0-10.0 UI range and are mapped to shader-specific ranges in `apply_uniforms()`.

| Parameter | Shader Uniform | Default | Mapped Range | Description |
|-----------|----------------|---------|--------------|-------------|
| `amount` | `amount` | 5.0 | 0.0-1.0 (divide by 10) | Blend strength: how much of the previous frame to add |
| `channel_mask` | `channel_mask` | 0.0 | 0-4 (0=all, 1=R, 2=G, 3=B, 4=luma) | Which color channels to use from previous frame |
| `boost` | `boost` | 5.0 | 0.5-3.0 (linear map) | Brightness multiplier applied to added signal |
| `offset_x` | `offset_x` | 5.0 | -0.2 to 0.2 (centered) | Horizontal UV offset for previous frame |
| `offset_y` | `offset_y` | 5.0 | -0.2 to 0.2 (centered) | Vertical UV offset for previous frame |
| `luma_mask` | `luma_mask` | 0.0 | 0.0-1.0 (divide by 10) | Only blend where current frame luma > threshold |

**Mapping Formulas:**
```python
amt = amount / 10.0
cm = channel_mask / 10.0 * 4.0
bst = 0.5 + boost / 10.0 * 2.5
off = (param / 10.0 - 0.5) * 0.4
lm = luma_mask / 10.0
```

